SIMPLE: imbitter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imbitter
<hw>Im*bit"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Imbittered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imbittering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>bitter</ets>. Cf. <er>Embitter</er>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>embitter</asp>.]</altsp> <def>To make bitter;
hence, to make distressing or more distressing; to make sad, morose,
sour, or malignant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is there anything that more <qex>imbitters</qex> the enjoyment of
this life than shame?</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Imbittered</qex> against each other by former contests.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbitterer</ent>⟦br⟧
